Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty for the offense of speeding. I am deeply sorry for the danger that I caused to those around me by engaging in reckless driving. 

I am 26 years old, and I admit that I have previous penalty points on my license from three speeding incidents. However, this offense is the result of my own impulsive decision to test the speed of my brand-new car. I acknowledge that it was an irresponsible and foolish act, and I take full responsibility for my actions.

I would like to bring to the court's attention that I have no criminal record apart from the driving offenses. I understand the seriousness of this offense and assure the court that I have reflected on my actions and their consequences. 

Furthermore, I have been diagnosed with ADHD, which may have influenced my decision-making abilities in this instance. I have sought appropriate treatment and support to manage this condition and prevent any future episodes of impulsive behavior. 

I genuinely regret not seeing the Notice of Intended Prosecution in the mail. However, I want to assure the court that if I had been aware of it, I would have promptly responded and cooperated with the authorities. 

In light of my plea of guilt, I would like to express my sincere remorse for my actions. I understand that my actions were unacceptable and put others at risk. I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience and I am committed to making amends.

I am willing to take proactive steps to prevent the recurrence of such offenses. I have already enrolled in advanced driving courses to improve my awareness and responsibility on the road. Additionally, I am actively contributing to society through my work and involvement in community service projects.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I acknowledge the seriousness of my offense and present myself before the court with honesty and humility. I ask for leniency in my sentencing, considering my plea of guilt, no extensive criminal history, and my efforts to address any underlying factors that may have influenced my actions. I am committed to learning from this experience and becoming a responsible member of society. Thank you for your attention.

