Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty for the offense of speeding. I want to express my sincere remorse for the danger that I caused to those around me by engaging in reckless driving.

I am 26 years old and acknowledge that I have previous penalty points on my license from three speeding incidents. However, this offense is the result of my own impulsive decision to test the speed of my brand-new car. I acknowledge that it was an irresponsible and foolish act, and I take full responsibility for my actions.

I want to assure the court that I have reflected on my actions and their consequences. I understand the seriousness of this offense and genuinely regret the danger I inflicted on others.

Additionally, I have been diagnosed with ADHD, which may have influenced my decision-making abilities in this instance. I have sought appropriate treatment and support to manage this condition and prevent any future episodes of impulsive behavior.

I genuinely regret not seeing the Notice of Intended Prosecution in the mail. However, I want to assure the court that if I had been aware of it, I would have promptly responded and cooperated with the authorities.

In light of my plea of guilt, I want to express my sincere remorse. I understand that my actions were unacceptable and put others at risk. I acknowledge the seriousness of my offense and present myself before the court in humility and honesty.

Thank you for your attention.
